Azure Content Delivery Network (CDN) handles requests by caching content at edge locations closer to users.

When a user requests content:

1. The request is routed to the nearest edge server
2. If cached, content is served directly
3. If not, it is fetched from the origin server

For example, images on a website are delivered quickly using CDN.

A real-life use case is streaming platforms delivering video content globally.

Another example is reducing load on backend servers by caching frequently accessed data.

CDN improves performance, scalability, and user experience.
